# Load the data schema 75 cols

# Define path

path = "abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/exports/monthly/ACMMonthlyActualCost/20220401-20220430/Extended_ACMMonthlyActualCost_20220401-20220430.parquet"
# Load the data schema 76 cols
#df_schema3 = spark.read.format("parquet").load(path)#.toPandas()
## Load all ACMMonthlyActualCost data and append to one dataframe.

import pandas as pd
from pyspark.sql.functions import lit
# Create a SparkSession
spark = SparkSession.builder.getOrCreate()

# Define an empty schema
schema = df_schema1.schema

# Create an empty DataFrame with the specified schema
df = spark.createDataFrame([], schema)
root_path = "abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/exports/monthly/ACMMonthlyActualCost"
folders = mssparkutils.fs.ls(root_path)

for folder in folders:
    file_paths = mssparkutils.fs.ls(root_path +'/'+ str(folder.name))

    for file_path in file_paths:
        if '.parquet' in file_path.name:
            try:
                date = pd.to_datetime(folder.path.split('/')[-1].split('-')[0],format="%Y/%m/%d")
                df_temp = spark.read.format("parquet").load(file_path.path)
                df_temp= df_temp.withColumn('Report_Date', lit(date))
                #df_temp = df_temp.withColumn('Report_Date', lit(date))
                df = df.union(df_temp)
                
            except Exception as e:
                print("The data can not be read",file_path.path)
